column5: Yet again another great night on the water... the weather lately has been unpredictable.. as you can see in the picture of Sonny running behind us... Be careful out there and always remember if you are fishing alone, have that life jacket on...   As always the kids had a great time... and fishing beside us Sherri caught her personal best Walleye at just over 10lbs.  Way to go !     Little Jigger adds that he didn't even have to jig for these ones... lol...  Cheers Jen

Thanks for the report Jen. I was going to make the trip down last week but with the winds being so high I'm glad I went north instead. Your still catching some great fish down there, Thanks for the report and pics.  Mike
VERY nice fish. I have 3 hours tomorrow to catch a couple while drifting some worm harness. I hope to I can do half as good as you did.
Great report Jen.  Looks like you all did very well.  Water was a bit rough for sure.  Joey
Have you noticed that the lake isn't that rough when the fishing is good
Great report and pics Jen  Great lookin eyes and congratulation to Sherri for her PB  Thanks for sharing Leechman
